***Call to urge Rep. David P. Joyce to oppose HR 620, the ADA Education and Reform Act. It is unacceptable to make individuals with disabilities responsible for ensuring businesses comply with the ADA.
***Call in support of S. 1689 Marijuana Justice Act of 2017. The government should be focused on fighting the opiate epidemic, not cracking down on legal marijuana businesses.

***Call to urge Rep. David P. Joyce to strenuously oppose the new CMS guidance allowing states to impose work requirements for Medicaid. Work requirements do not increase employment over time, and denying needy people access to healthcare will only worsen poverty in the US.
***Call to demand that Rep. David Joyce support Rep. Richmond and Nadler's Resolution to censure Trump for his racist comments made in about Africa and Haiti.
***Ask Rep. David P. Joyce to support HR 2670 the Protecting Domestic Violence and Stalking Victims Act, and HR 3207 the Zero Tolerance for Domestic Abusers Act.

***Call to express your serious opposition to the EPA's decision to repeal the Clean Power Plan.  Strongly urge Rep. David P. Joyce to support measures that uphold the strategies of the Clean Power Plan and oppose those that undermine it.
*** Demand Protection of our National Monuments ***Support of H.R. 4570, the Ending Forced Arbitration of Sexual Harassment Act of 2017.

***Ask Rep. David P. Joyce to support a clean DREAM Act and reject Trumps demands to include massive, unnecessary spending on border security to the bill. It is unfair and immoral to use the lives of hundreds of thousands of young DACA recipients as bargaining chips.

***Ask Joyce to support S. 200 and H.R. 669, bills that would prevent the president from launching a nuclear first strike before Congress has passed a declaration of war. Together, the bills send the clear message that America will not be a nuclear aggressor.
